        "authorId" : "82da2b23-9f40-4abd-8af5-56ba07c1fc0a",
        "body" : "Random question: is it possible to have HPA enabled when you are doing rolling update? how does it work?\n",
        "createdAt" : "2015-10-18T08:43:04Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2015-10-26T07:37:07Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "82da2b23-9f40-4abd-8af5-56ba07c1fc0a",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "a74320df-16d4-4fda-bf3d-27eb0b8ff7c3",
        "parentId" : "52f6a7c7-9607-4b1c-8027-32ef8a252cdd",
        "authorId" : "c929c906-4dfb-433b-9bc7-1b4b05c176f8",
        "body" : "If rolling update is done by deployment and HPA is bind to the deployment: it should be compatible with HPA (we just resize the deployment).\n\nIf rolling update is done in an old way, by kubectl rolling-update, and HPA is bind to RC, it will not work as rolling update will create a new RC (not bind to HPA).\n\nDo you want me to extend the doc and describe it somehow?\n",
        "createdAt" : "2015-10-19T09:21:37Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2015-10-26T07:37:07Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "c929c906-4dfb-433b-9bc7-1b4b05c176f8",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "769fdab1-35ab-4436-9f2a-999c7009cfcd",
        "parentId" : "52f6a7c7-9607-4b1c-8027-32ef8a252cdd",
        "authorId" : "82da2b23-9f40-4abd-8af5-56ba07c1fc0a",
        "body" : "Yeah I feel like we should say something about this ... maybe it belongs in he user guide instead of here, but seems like we should warn users about incompatibility between HPA and RC rolling update\n\n@bgrant0607 for comment.\n",
        "createdAt" : "2015-10-20T07:57:34Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2015-10-26T07:37:07Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "82da2b23-9f40-4abd-8af5-56ba07c1fc0a",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
